South African white maize futures prices hit 11-month highs on Monday as a spell of hot, dry weather raised concerns about plantings and yields over a swathe of the maize belt. The contract for delivery in March rose over 2% to R2 123.80 a ton, its highest level in 11 months, before easing back to be 1.35% higher at R2 098, according to Reutersâ€™ data. 